{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"reviewer\":\"codex\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"scores\":null,\"weightedTotal\":null,\"verdict\":\"WARNING\",\"issues\":[{\"severity\":\"P3\",\"location\":\"src/components/dashboard/delete-space-section.tsx:31\",\"description\":\"If a persisted space has an empty name, the confirmation input starts as an exact match, so the destructive delete button is enabled immediately without any typing. Normal create/settings UI mostly prevents this, but the backend PATCH path does not enforce non-empty names, so this is a real data-drift edge in the UI guard.\",\"recommendation\":\"Require a non-empty confirmation token before enabling delete, for example `spaceName.length > 0 && confirmInput === spaceName`, and render a safe fallback/error state for empty names.\",\"defer\":false,\"deferRationale\":null,\"fixNow\":true},{\"severity\":\"P3\",\"location\":\"src/components/dashboard/delete-space-section.tsx:92\",\"description\":\"The modal sets `role=\\\"dialog\\\"`, `aria-modal`, and autofocus, but it does not trap focus or restore focus to the opener. Keyboard users can tab to controls behind the modal while it is visually modal.\",\"recommendation\":\"Use the existing Radix Dialog dependency or add a small focus-trap/focus-restore implementation so tab focus stays inside the dialog until it closes.\",\"defer\":false,\"deferRationale\":null,\"fixNow\":false}]}"}}
